    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to ornamental devices of any kind, especially grilles or lattices, fitted into window openings. In the United States the term more specifically refers to screens of mesh designed to be put across window openings to admit air while excluding insects.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000010761/Harris, Dictionary of Architecture and Construction (1975)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar ornamenten, met name roosters of traliewerken, die in een vensteropening zijn aangebracht. Verwijst naar schermen met gaas die voor ramen worden geplaatst om insecten buiten te houden maar wel buitenlucht toe te laten.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指窗戶開口處裝設的各種裝飾構件，特別是格柵或花格狀柵。該詞彙在美國，則特別指設於窗戶開口處，可保持通風但能阻絕蚊蟲進入的網狀屏幕。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
